    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Another win for CNNs!</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">Cold Diffusion (August 2022)</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Of course I had to mention Diffusion somehow in 2022. But I hope is not in the way that everyone thinks about it like <a href="https://openaccess.thecvf.com/content/CVPR2022/papers/Rombach_High-Resolution_Image_Synthesis_With_Latent_Diffusion_Models_CVPR_2022_paper.pdf" target="_self">Stable Diffusion</a> or <a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2111.05826.pdf" target="_self">Palette</a> and so on. The paper I‚Äôm going to show is about <strong>the generalization of the Diffusion process</strong>. We all know Diffusion proces, right? You first take an image and add Gaussian Noise slowly until is pretty much just noise. Then remove it slowly using the magic of AI until the original image is reconstructed. If you learn to do this for a long time you can sample just noise and make the network slowly ‚Äúimagine‚Äù what is in there. So seems like the key word is <strong>noise</strong>.<strong> </strong>Or is it‚Ä¶</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
