            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">What?! Already over? But‚Ä¶ it happend so fast‚Ä¶ Okay, how about some quick honorable mentions that for some arbitrary reason didn‚Äôt make the cut. Maybe I‚Äôm just trying to delay the goodbye as much as possible, but I think they are worth a mention:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ul><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2207.09238.pdf" target="_self">Formal Algortithms for Transformers</a><strong> (July 2022):</strong> So you like Transformers, uh? Alright, okay‚Ä¶ There you go, the <strong>Holy Bible of Transformers</strong>, thank me later. This paper contains a bunch of transformer architectures and algoritms with the mathematics included. They also explain what Transformers are and what do they do in a very nice and understandable way. This should be the way-to-go guide for every average Transfomers user.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2110.12661.pdf" target="_self">ZerO Initialization</a><strong> (November 2022):</strong> This paper introduces an <strong>inizialization method using only deterministic 0 and 1 instead of random weights</strong>. This simple thing allows for training ‚Äúultra deep‚Äù networks without Batch Normalization and resulting in low-rank learning trajectories and sparse solutions. Also, as the network inizialization is not random, it improves reproducibility!</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2211.06956.pdf" target="_self">Seeing Beyond the Brain</a><strong> (November 2022):</strong> This is a personal favourite from 2022. It‚Äôs quite surreal to think that using mask modeling and diffusion one can <strong>decode the images that a person is thinking of via MRI! </strong>Wow. Brain reading State of the Art 2022 I guess.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><a href="https://phenaki.video/#interactive" target="_self">Phenaki</a><strong> (November 2022):</strong> Text-to-Image models are trending and there has been <a href="https://medium.com/@diegobonila/text-to-image-papers-to-read-in-summer-2022-c57c7c9f1044" target="_self">a lot</a> of papers about it (shameless plug). But if there is something that could get us closer to the first movie made by an AI is‚Ä¶ <strong>Text-to-Video! </strong>This paper explains how to make videos from static and <strong>dynamic text</strong>. What is dynamic text? A script for example, or a set of instructions that you want the video to follow in time. They even generated short movies of <strong>2:30 minutes</strong>! Wow.</li></ul></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
